The paper discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for learning data distributions, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on the use of regularized Optimal Transport (OT) in GANs, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.IT.
